Edo Dynamos, Borno Spiders and Benue Queens recorded victories, yesterday, to continue their battle for promotion to the Handball Premier League.
In match Day Three games at the ongoing National Division One League holding in Benin City, Edo State, Edo Dynamos defeated Owena Kings 27 to 25, while Borno Spiders overwhelmed Mindscope Academy 26 to 17. In the women class, Benue Queens outmuscled Delta Force 31 to 27 also in an exciting faceoff, while the confrontation between Suleja Shooters and Police Machine ended in a 22 to 22 draw. The competition continues today at the same venue.